comment_data.body:
I don't think this is exactly the right guard.

`PyType_TryGetSubSlot` will work with `CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS` both true and false. (Although it'll return NULL for non-heaptypes in runtime versions < 3.10 when `CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS` is false).

`CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS` is really guarding direct access into the type object.

I think you want something like:

```
#if !CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS && __PYX_LIMITED_API_VERSION_HEX < 0x030A0000
if (__pyx_get_runtime_version() < 0x030A0000 && PyType_GetFlags(type_op2, Py_TPFLAGS_HEAPTYPE)) {
    return return {{op_name}}(op1, op2);
}
#else
// ... code as below, but you can use `__Pyx_PyType_GetSubSlot` because you don't have to guard against the heaptype case.
```

